simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function indicates whether the Dwell Table corresponding to the input table pointer is valid.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: This function gets registered with Table Services as a callback function for validating Dwell Tables that are loaded from the ground, and so must be in accordance with the call signature specified by Table Services. In addition, the function is used by Memory Dwell to validate Dwell Tables that have been recovered from a Critical Data Store.

entry.para: Enable flag in table load is invalid (valid values are 0 and 1)
Table has zero value for total delay, and at least one dwell specified.
Dwell address improperly aligned for specified dwell length.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Read active entries and count number of dwell addresses, number of bytes to be dwelled on, and number of wakeup calls between sending of dwell packets.

parameterdescription.para: Number of addresses to be sampled.
Size, in bytes, of data to be sampled.
Rate, in number of wakeup calls, between sending of dwell packets.

briefdescription.para: Validate dwell entries in specified Dwell Table.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Validate memory ranges for dwell address and field length, and validate field length size for entries in specified Dwell Table.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: For table to be valid, each entry must be a null entry (specified by a zero field length) or the entry's address and length field must pass various checks.

parameterdescription.para: Entry number (0..) of first detected error, if any.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Validates whether specified dwell table entry is valid.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: To be valid, entry must either be a null entry (specified by a zero field length) or all of its address and length fields must pass various checks.

entry.para: Dwell address improperly aligned for specified dwell length.

briefdescription.para: Generate internal data structures based on Dwell Table Load.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Copies Enabled field. Copies Signature field. For each dwell table entry, copies field length, and delay value. Evaluates and saves resolved dwell address for each dwell entry. Evaluates and saves additional summary data based on entry contents.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: Dwell table contents have been validated before reaching this point. Run when a table is loaded by command, or when a table is recovered on start up.

parameterdescription.para: An identifier specifying which dwell table is to be copied. Internal values [0..MD_NUM_DWELL_TABLES-1] are used.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: TableIndex is in [0..MD_NUM_DWELL_TABLES-1] range. FieldValue is MD_DWELL_STREAM_ENABLED or MD_DWELL_STREAM_DISABLED.

parameterdescription.para: An identifier specifying which dwell table is to be modified. Internal values [0..MD_NUM_DWELL_TABLES-1] are used.
